    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bases of Ionic columns following a pattern developed in Asia Minor, with an upper torus surmounting a disk generally composed of shallow scotias, both elements being usually horizontally fluted.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor de basementen van Ionische zuilen met een patroon dat in Klein Azië is ontwikkeld. Ze hebben een bovenste torus die op een schijf van ondiepe scheppende holen rust, waarbij beide elementen meestal horizontaal zijn gecanneleerd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052396/Koch, Europese bouwstijlen (1988)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bases de colunas jônicas seguindo um padrão desenvolvido na Ásia Menor, com um toro superior encimando um disco geralmente composto por escócias rasas, sendo ambos os elementos geralmente canelados horizontalmente.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Basis einer ionischen Säule mit einem oberen Torus über flachen Hohlkehlen; beide Elemente sind üblicherweise mit horizontalen Rillen versehen. Die Form stammt aus Kleinasien.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
